data.text:
30. Juri Takahashi (AKB48  Team 4 Captain).

Although Aki Takajo graduated in February, she was to continue doing AKB48 events til the end of May. Ive said I was going to continue to ranked her til that time, will I change my mind. I wont be ranking her anymore, so it left a position for someone else to come in here. 2 members I considered it was very close between those two, I choose Juri for no reason except I felt like it.

Shes been ranked her before, but not since Ive change this to the AKB48 family ranking (It used to be just AKB48 members). More than a couple of years ago, back then she was so cute and kinda funny looking, now shes kinda hot looking. Back then I could not imagine seeing her in a bikini, now she looks really hot in it. Ive gotten back to following her a little bit for almost a year now. 29. Nanase Nishino (Nogizaka46  1st Generation).

I dont know what it is with her, I just get hypnotize by her everytime I look at her. 28. Minami Takahashi (AKB48  Team A).

She will be saying Bye-Bye to AKB48 very soon. Her graduation concert was a few days ago, and her last theater performance will be April 8th. Which just happens to be her Birthday.

Happy 25th Birthday in advance, Takamina. 27. Minami Minegishi (AKB48  Team K Captain). 26. Sayuri Matsumura (Nogizaka46  1st Generation). 25. Rena Kato (AKB48  Team B).

I just still cant get over with how beautiful and sexy she has become. 24. Miori Ichikawa (NMB48  Team BII).

Im not really seeing and hearing much of Lemon lately, make that kinda long lately. 23. JingYi Ju (SNH48 -Team NII). 22. Yuria Kizaki (AKB48  Team B Captain).

I still cant get over her rise and understand how it happen, to where she is now. 21. Nanami Hashimoto (Nogizaka46  1st Generation).

Her hair in longer now, I dont know how long she will let it grow. She looks really pretty, I dont know if I prefer her with short hair or not. She looks beautiful either way. 20. ZheHan Wu (SNH48  Team SII and Team X).

Ive mention this before, I think she really looks like Yurina Kumai. 19. Haruka Kodama (HKT48  Team H and AKB48  Team K).

18. Ryoha Kitagawa (SKE48  Team S and AKB48  Team 4). 17. Rie Kitahara (NGT48 Captain  Team NIII).

I just listen to AKB48 single Kimi wa Melody, on Type D NGT48 has a song Max Toki 315go. Which I really like alot, hope they release a single sooner than later. 16. Rino Sashihara (HKT48  Team H and HKT48 Theater Manager). 15. Mion Mukaichi (AKB48  Team K). 14. Sumire Sato (SKE48  Team E). 13. JiaMin Zhao (SNH48  Team SII).

I think shes still on hiatus, hope she returns soon. I think shes done a few photoshoots while shes been on hiatus from SNH48. 12. Haruka Shimazaki (AKB48  Team A).

March 30th, is her Birthday. Happy 22nd Birthday, Paruru. 11. Sakura Miyawaki (HKT48  Team KIV Co Captain and AKB48  Team A).

Last year I mention I couldnt believe how much she had grown, I think she grew some more. She looks like a giant next to some members.

March 19th, was her Birthday. Happy belated 18th Birthday, Sakura. 10. Anna Iriyama (AKB48  Team A). 9. Aika Oota (HKT48  Team KIV Captain). 8. Sayaka Yamamoto (NMB48  Team N Captain and AKB48  Team K). 7. Miyuki Watanabe (NMB48  Team BII and AKB48  Team B). 6. Mayu Watanabe (AKB48  Team B).

Shes suppose to be releasing her 6th single soon this year, for a while now I having heard anything about it.

A few days ago March 26th, was her Birthday. Happy belated 22nd Birthday, Mayuyu. 5. Meru Tashima (HKT48  Team H). 4. Kei Jonishi (NMB48  Team N Co Captain).

March 18th, was her Birthday. Happy belated 21st Birthday, Keicchi.

Keicchi, You want to know what I was doing on your Birthday.

3. Mai Shiraishi (Nogizaka46  1st Generation). 2. Yuki Kashiwagi (AKB48  Team B and NGT48  Team NIII) 1. Haruna Kojima (AKB48  Team A).

Im kinda rushing this, so Im not giving this much though. I just want to get this done by the end of this month, I just hope Im not overlooking anyone.

Ill try to make a comment of something of interest, if not Ill just comment when I started to like them or why I do.

I do this twive a month in January and July.

My Top 25 Favorite J-Pop Idols, singers, etc.

25. Maria Makino (Morning Musume).

I first notice her earlier last year, I find her very attractive and sexually appealing. I shouldnt say something like that about someone so young, Pretty girl.

On February 2nd, itll be her birthday. Happy 15th Birthday in advance, Maria. 24. Rika Mayama (Shiritsu Ebisu Chuugaku).

Ive known her way before this, but I started to really take interest in her in very early 2014. I was watching alot of Shiritsu Ebisu Chuugaku videos around that time, I just found her so funny. Shed always make all these funny/weird gestures, thats the reason why I basically like her shes always making these gestures. She is also kinda cute. 23. Rina Matsuno (Shiritsu Ebisu Chuugaku).

I noticed her cause she was tall and being kinda cute help also, I have a weakness for tall females. I wouldnt say shes really that tall, in the J-Pop Idol world. Shes really tall. 22. Rika Tonosaki (Doll Elements).

Ive known Doll Elements for about 2 years or so, I guess. Shes the member who I would always notice, although I thought she was super cute. I really had no intention of wanting to get interested in her, until about 2 months. It doesnt look like it, she has pretty big Boobs. I dont know if this a turn off or I actually like it, she hasnt change abit the last few years. Yeah, Ive been fantasizing about her quite abit lately. 21. Rio Watanabe (Babyraids JAPAN).

I think her dancing is better, she used to dance very awkwardly and was always a step behind the other members. I think her dancing better.

I think shes super cool, the kind of person I like to hang out and talk with. 20. Karin Ogino (Yumemiru Adolescence).

I find her really annoying , but in a cute and likeable way. I dont think Ill ever get bored of her, theirs a reason why I wrote that. 19. Sayaka Yamamoto (NMB48 and AKB48).

She can paly the guitar pretty good, Im not bad myself. I would love to jam with her play some NMB and AKB songs, that would be fun. 18. Nao Sakura (Team Syachihoko).

I think she might be the J-Pop idol, I think I would like to hang out with the most. Her birthday is a day after mine. 17. Kanna Hashimoto (Rev. from DVL).

Ill be honest I didnt think her 15 minutes of fame would last this long, shes a real cutie so Im glad it did. I bough her photobook, and she has a solo single Sailor Fuku to Kikanjuu which will be release on February 23rd. Ill probably will buy that also.

On February 3rd, is her birthday. Happy 17th Birthday in advance, Kanna. 16. Mayu Watanabe (AKB48).

My interest in her has been diminishing a little bit the last year, maybe longer than that. Maybe because I dont find her to be annoyingly cute anymore, she seems more mature. It just might be me, I dont know. Doing alot more bikini photoshoot would fix that problem, which I think shes been doing lately. It seem like their was a time she was barely doing any at all. 15. Yuna Sekine (Cheeky Parade).

Cheeky Parades fearless and emotional Leader. Yes, I would love to see her and Cheeky Parade again. 14. Miyuki Watanabe (NMB48 and AKB48).

I dont know what it is with Milky and me, just when it looks like Im starting to lose interest in her (Its happen a few times). Before I know it, it goes way back up again. 13. Kanako Momota (Momoiro Clover Z).

I really dont know what to say abour her except she has the cutest smile and dimples (Lovetan may disagree). 12. Meru Tashima (HKT48).

Im still not sure if shes putting on some weight or just developing, cause Ive seen some recent pictures. It looks like shes getting a little fat, I just remember a couple of years ago. She was so skinny. 11. Haruna Iikubo (Morning Musume).

Shes all sex appeal, to me. Im actually getting a little excited about her right now. 10. Kei Jonishi (NMB48).

What can I say about her, I havent already say here. If I were to have a J-Pop beauty pageant, she would win. 9. Mai Shiraishi (Nogizaka46).

Is it me, it seems like shes doing alot less activities and stuff compared to before. It seem like she was everywhere before. 8. Asami Watanabe (Cheeky Parade).

Ive fantasize about having a J-Pop Idol as a girlfriend many times before, but never being married to one. The last few weeks maybe longer, Ive been fantasizing about being married to Asami alot. My imagination can get very wild. I would love to do a threesome with this two. 7. Miki Shimomura (Fairies).

I think shes a tease and likes to flirt, in her good Miki way. 6. Seran Mizorogi (Cheeky Parade).

Whatever it was I was feeling about her, the last time I did this ranking its over. Thank goodness, it was only temporary. It had more to do with Miki Shimomura, with my interest in her probably at an all time high.

I think she has change her hairstyle, I didnt like it at first. In fact it was a turn off, Im actually liking it now. 5. Yukafin Doll (Afilia Saga).

This sucks Yukafin Doll is graduating from Afilia Saga, I think sometime in early February. Ayami Chercy Snow & Louise Sforzur is also leaving the group around that time, Yukafin Doll is about the only reason that Im even remotely interested in Afilia Saga. I really dont why theyre an enjoyable group to watch and quite a few cute members. 4. Ai Negishi (PASSPO).

It seems like her and PASSPO that a quiet 2015, they were actually very active. Im not sure about this, I think I read somewhere that she was releasing a photobook sometime this year. I hope so the 2 she release so far were really good. 3. Hitomi Arai (Tokyo Girls Style).

She still has that very sweet smile, and is as cute as ever. Sometimes I get that feeling shes more serious now, maybe shes just starting to grow up. Now that I think about it, she was always kinda like that. 2. Yuki Kashiwagi (AKB48 and NGT48).

Its seems alot longer, it was almost exactly about 5 years ago that I first notice her. I dont think their ever was one picture that I saw that has had more of an impact on me, than that one I saw of her that night. Huh, What? 1. Haruna Kojima (AKB48).

When it comes to her I rarely make any comments, and really dont talk like shes my infinite absolute favorite. I do have a pretty good Kojima collection I think I have all her photobooks and I buy magazines with her on the cover, just to name a few. Ooh, How could I forget her calendars. ____________________________________________________________________

My Top 20 J-Pop Groups.

20. Idol Renaissance.

It look about a minute to consider who to put at this position, a lot of candidates. A second to decide, it wasnt an easy one, had to chose one, and do it quickly.

Ive know Idol Renaissance for well over a year, I like their songs. The members are really cute, especially a couple of them.

19. Country Girls.

They were formed just a little more than a year ago, they already had one member graduate and added two new members late last year. Those two new members look kinda cute. They release two singles so far which I really like alot, and a new one coming very soon. I just enjoy watching them theyre so refreshing. 18. Tokyo Girls Style.

On late December 2015 Ayano Konishi, official left the group, I prefer them as five. Oh well, nothing I can do about it. I dont know why they have a problem with being called an Idol group, Fairies doesnt. Then again I dont think anyone really calls or considers Fairies an Idol Group, atleast not techically. 17. Team Syachihoko.

For a while my interest in them was diminishing, lately Im starting to really get interested in them again also with their leader Honoka Akimoto, who I seriously considered including her back again. 16. C-ute.

Anytime I have a friends who doesnt know anything about J-Pop, this the group I usually recommend or mention first. 15. Fairies.

Have they ever done any overseas activities outside of Asia? Miki is my favorite, but Ive been really liking Rikako Inoue for several months now. 14. 9nine.

I really like them alot as a group, although their was really no one particular member I really had any interest in even remotely following. Uki Satake probably came the closes. I guess almost a month now Ive been very interested in Umika Kawashima, I mean Ive been fantasizing about her alot. For a time there, almost on a daily basis.

With Babyraids JAPAN.

13. Babyraids JAPAN.

Another J-Pop Idol group, which to me seem like they were doing less activities, compared to previous years. I think theyve reach their peak a while ago, I hope they have a very good 2016. If you asked me 2015 was a disapointment, in the sense it could have been alot better. With Yumemiru Adolescence. 12. SKE48.

I dont know why I dont like or follow SKE48 alot more than I should, of all the groups in the AKB48 family. I think theyre the group that have remained the most constant (Graduations not included), and they have alot of really cute members. When I do check them out they never disappoint, I should be checking them out alot more. 11. NMB48.

What I said about SKE48, is the opposite of NMB48. I check them out alot more than SKE48, more times than not I fine them rather boring. Theyre more consistent than SKE48 in every sense, maybe thats why I like them more. 10. Shiritsu Ebisu Chuugaku.

If they release more stuff, they would probably rank higher. Theyre very entertaining, almost second to none. They just dont have enough stuff lately to keep me entertain. 9. Nogizaka46.

Nogizaka46 as a new sister group Toriizaka46, it was bound to happen. If they turn out anything like Nogizaka46, I guess its good. On average theyre pretty young, some really cute members. 8. Yumemiru Adolescence.

I dont think I get excited as much as when an Idol Group releases a new single, as much as I do with this group. An Kyouka is growing up to be very fine young woman. 7. PASSPO.

The lost 2 members in 2015 due to graduation, Makoto Okunaka at the start of the year and Sako Makita at the end of the year. 2 members that I really like a lot.

Do they ever do a lot of concerts. 6. HKT48.

Not that I didnt in the past, but lately Ive checking them out a fair amount times lately. Wow, some of those members have really grown up. Some are just dead gorgeous, will be checking them out a fair amount of times now. This didnt happen yesterday, I dont why I didnt notice this before. Maybe I did I was just too lazy and uninterested or to bothered to notice. I can be like that sometimes. 5. SUPER GiRLS.

Sometime this year I was a little worried, my interest in them was probably at an all time low. Thanks, to Rina Miyazaki and maybe a couple of others its back to where it should be. They just need to be in the spotlight more, like they used to be. To me it seems like theyre not trying, for it. 4. Momoiro Clover Z.

Theyre releasing 2 albums in February will definitely get both. 3. Morning Musume.

On December 31, 2015. Riho Sayashi graduated from the group, which is to bad. She was a cutie.

Next month they will be at Anime Matsuri, in Houston, Texas. Its not 100%, but its looking good that I will be attending it. 2. Cheeky Parade.

Im not to sure exactly what this is all about but Marin Yamamoto and Mariya Suzuki, will going on a 2 year hiatus from Cheeky Parade. To study abroad in Los Angeles, California. Another member from their sister group GEM, Maaya takeda is also going with them. I dont think a date as been announced when They will be leaving. 1. AKB48.

My only complain about them is sometimes when I watch them, its not like watching AKB48. I hope you know what I mean, Unlike SKE48, NMB48 and HKT48. *Got done on time, at a second to spare.

Ive done this before but it was a long while ago, for this month comments. Ill just write about when I started to like them, or notice them or got interested in them. If just a little.

30. Nanase Nishino (Nogizaka46  1st Generation).

I guess the first time I kinda notice her was almost 2 years when she was going to become Center for a Nogizaka46 single, she was also getting a fair amount of attention around that time. I just remember wondering what all the fuss was about her, anyways I really didnt start to really like her until a few months ago. I just think she seem really nice and sweet. 29. Rena Kato (AKB48  Team B).

It was March or April 2011, I was watching an AKB48 concert video from 2010. I just remember how cute she really look, she was the first non official AKB48 member I was really interested in. 28. Minami Takahashi (AKB48  Team A).

I notice her right from the beginning although I couldnt tell the difference her and Yuko Oshima, it took about a couple of weeks for me to tell the 2 apart. 27. Minami Minegishi (AKB48  Team K Captain).

I notice her almost from the beginning, and like her right away. She was so funny and playful and kinda mouthy.

26. Sayuri Matsumura (Nogizaka46  1st Generation).

It was either very late 2011 or very early 2012, I think it had something to do with promoting their 1st single. She was one of the first member that caught my eye, she was really cute and I just loved her hair. 25. Miori Ichikawa (NMB48  Team BII).

I first noticed her the same video that I first notice Renacchi in, she was so cute and tiny. She was so awkwardly funny I just couldnt stop laughing, even now for some reason when I see her. I just start to laugh.

24. JingYi Ju (SNH48  Team NII).

It was a year ago when I started to get back to follwing SNH48 again for a 3rd time, at that time it was just the 1st Generation members that I mainly knew. When I saw her I though she was really pretty, check her out. It hasnt really stop since. 23. Yuria Kizaki (AKB48  Team B Captain).

Thats a good question, I really dont know or remember. I think I remember seeing her in late 2011, she was really cute. But like almost every SKE48 member at the time I just didnt bother checking her out or try even remotely to get interested in her. I guess it was almost a year ago that I started to like her and started paying more attention to her. 22. Aki Takajo (AKB48  Team K).

I notice her and was very attracted to her almost from the beginning, I couldnt keep my eyes off her. 21. Nanami Hashimoto (Nogizaka46  1st Generation).

I started to really notice and get interested in her around the summer of 2013, she was going to star on a TV show and she was also getting alot of attention around that time, or atleast it seem like to me. 20. ZheHan Wu (SNH48  Team SII and Team X).

When she was number one in SNH48 1st Senbatsu Election (2014), that was a surprise for me. So I kinda did some checking on her, I though she was very pretty I can see why she was on Top. Then I kinda forgot about her, when SNH48 released Give Me Five in January 2015. I though she look great in the video and I kinda fell in love with her. Unfortunately she got into a scandal not too long after that, not that I cared. It was just that for several months I really didnt see or hear too much about her, as far has SNH48 events or activities goes. 19. Haruka Kodama (HKT48  Team H and AKB48 Team K).

I notice her right from the beginning as she promoted to be HKT48 Center, I really didnt start to really like her and get very interested in her until early 2014. 18. Ryoka Kitagawa (SKE48  Team S and AKB48  Team 4).

I remember seeing her on the CD Cover of SKE48 single Sansei Kawaii!, which was released on November 2013. She was still a Research Student Ive never her before, but she was really pretty. Around early 2014 she was getting alot of heavy pushing, considering how pretty I though she was. It was very hard not to notice and get interested in her. 17. Rie Kitahara (NGT48 Captain  Team NIII).

I notice her almost from the beginning, athough I knew they were 2 different person. For a couple months when ever I saw her I though it was Sasshi, yes it took me that long to tell them apart maybe longer than that. I wish she would do alot more bikini photoshoot, like she use to. 16. Rino Sashihara (HKT48  Team H and HKT48 Theater Manager).

When I first got into AKB48 her and Yui Yokoyama were probably the most heavily push members, shes so funny and entertaining it was hard not to notice and like her. 15. Mion Mukaichi (AKB48  Team K).

I still remember when it was August 2013, I was checking out AKB48 Research Students for reason (This is something I dont do). When I saw her it was love at first sight, since that time Ive been following her.

On January 29th, its her Birthday. Happy 18th Birthday in advance, Mion. Wow, its been that long she was only 15 when I first notice her. 14. Sumire Sato (SKE48  Team E).

I notice her way before this, but I just remember during AKB48 promoting their single Everyday, Katyusha she was involved in lot of the performance for the single. 13. JiaMin Zhao (SNH48  Team SII).

When SNH48 were first starting out she was promoted that she would be center, and she was getting the most attention or pushing. Lets be honest she was really cute back then, now days she has more of a mature look, but thats another story. It doesnt change anything.

12. Haruka Shimazaki (AKB48  Team A).

I guess it was around June 2012, she was getting alot of heavy pushing around this time. I just basically joined the bandwagon.

11. Sakura Miyawaki (HKT48  Team KIV and AKB48  Team A).

I though she was really funny looking at first, she look like a doll. I cant really remember when I started to really, really like her. She really as grown up. 10. Anna Iriyama (AKB48  Team A).

When did I start to notice, follow, get intertested and like her. When I saw AKB48 in Wahington D.C., in March 2012. I knew who she was way before this, but didnt take notice or cared too much of her. I think she has the most beautiful hair. 9. Aika Oota (HKT48  Team KIV Captain).

It was likely WH7 Valentine Kiss, in the beginning I used to fantasize about her and Mayu (After I started liking her) alot. 8. Sayaka Yamamoto (NMB48  Team N Captain and AKB48  Team K).

When I first saw AKB48 video Everyday, Katyusha, when I first saw her it was really love at first sight. I prefer her with long hair. 7. Mayu Watanabe (AKB48  Team B).

I notice her right from the beginning, although I really hated her the first 2 months or so. I just thought she was really funny looking and really weird. Shes the only AKB48 that I really hated, she was also so annoying. As soon has I got to know her abit more, the hating stop. 6. Miyuki Watanabe (NMB48  Team BII and AKB48  Team B).

I first heard of her around March 2011, she was the NMB48 member that all AKB48 fans were talking about. She was that first NMB48 member I knew, I didnt like her at first mainly because I was a Sayaka fan. It was around December 2011, that I just started to like her for some reason. I really dont know what happen, it was I just got up one morning and I was Milky fan. 5. Meru Tashima (HKT48  Team H).

I first heard of her around the release of HKT48 1st single Suki! Suki! Skip!, on March 2013. I wasnt really following HKT48 back then, she was center on the single and on the CD Cover of all them. I was like Who is she?, although I didnt really like Haruka Kodama that much at that time. I found this to a bit of a turn off for some reason, it was a great single. I didnt really start to like Meru until about a year later, I just find very refreshing.

Im very late on this. January 7th, was her Birthday. Happy Belated 16th Birthday, Meru. 4. Kei Jonishi (NMB48  Team N Co-Captain).

I mention this before I first saw her around the release of their 1st single, looking (Thinking) back it was actually the 2nd single. I was looking at some pictures of NMB48 it had something to do with the 2nd single, she just caught my eye. It wasnt really until early in 2012 that I got all crazy about her. 3. Mai Shiraishi (Nogizaka46  1st Generation).

It was very late 2011 or very early 2012, Nogizaka46 was doing quite abit of photo shoot. Basically promoting their 1st single, they were all cute. She was the one who I thought was the pretties. 2. Yuki Kashiwagi (AKB48  Team B and NGT48  Team NIII).

When it came to noticing her, I was a little slow. I didnt actually know who she was until a couple of weeks after I got into AKB48. I just saw this one picture of her she look really hot, when I found out who she was I did some searches on her. Shes hot, how come I never notice her before. 1. Haruna Kojima (AKB48  Team A).

I got into JPop 1st or 2nd day of 2011, I was still about 2 weeks after discovering AKB48. I came across the AKB48 single Chance no Junban, which was their latest single. The CD Cover the one with her on it, there was one person that really caught my eye she was funny looking and had big ears. Its hard to expalain the feeling, she was just most gorgeous thing Ive ever seen. When I started to get into AKB48, I saw that CD Cover again not to long after. Oh, I though she look familiar.
